Design notes for Amazon prototype shopping cart user sessions 

Reference : http://www.gridshore.nl/2011/07/28/combining-java-and-node-js-through-redis-pubsub-and-a-json-remote-interface/


Spring server takes the HTTP requests - GET , POST, PUT for now and writes the record to a query db and reflects the change in redis

Implementation Notes :- 

1)JSON response,Take a key value object from the http 
2)Current cart,payment design classes
3)DB calls - store,fetch , delete , update
4)Listener configuration - for the db and redis.

